MEASUREMENTS (
MM
). Length of body: 15.6–27.0; length of fore wing: 20.8–32.6; width of fore wing: 6.75–11.1; length of head: 3.05–4.2; width of head including eyes: 6.6–9.0; width of pronotum including suprahumeral plates: 5.8–8.7; width of mesonotum: 4.8–8.0.

DISTRIBUTION. The species is known only from 
Panama
(
Sanborn 2013
, 2018). Panamanian specimens were collected in lowland forest on Barro Colorado Island at 
120 m
altitude (
Ramos & Wolda 1985
; 
Wolda 1977
; 
1988
; 
1989
; 
1993
; 
Wolda & Ramos 1992
).
